node.text: Wishing the happiest birthday to our ultimate Wildlife Warrior, Terri! Your strength and perseverance has lead #AustraliaZoo and @wildlifewarriorsworldwide to accomplish milestones in the world of wildlife conservation. Thank you for working every single day to ensure Steve's passion and legacy continues. We love you! 💖

node.text:
Crikey! We wanted to send a big thank you to the family at @hoselinkofficial for helping us care for our world-class zoological gardens connecting our guests to nature.

Thank you for your support, making a difference in wildlife conservation! Check out the Cultivating Connections series featuring some of our favourite Australia Zoo animals!
#hoselink #cultivatingconnections

node.title: Hoselink Cultivating Connections with Australia Zoo

node.text: “On my evening motorbike ride I found this turtle a bit hung up in the fence next to a road and an alligator enclosure (not a safe place to be when you’re a little turtle!) So I took him for a ride on the bike and relocated him to a nearby waterhole. Hopefully Sheldon appreciated the rescue!” — @robertirwinphotography

node.text: Congratulations to our guests, Jesse and Erin, who popped the big question in the Crocoseum🎉 Are you planning that special moment this year? We’re here to help make it magical! From proposals to elopements, visit australiazoo.com.au and let the Crikey Crew help you say “I do!” ❤️ (Feel free to tag anyone who could use a little hint😊💍 )

node.text: Thank you for your extraordinary support during this profound year. As we embark on 2021, we are grateful for every joyful moment shared here at #AustraliaZoo. Wishing you a safe and happy New Year from the entire Australia Zoo Crew! 🎉

node.text: Did you hear the news? The #AustraliaZoo Wildlife Hospital has officially treated over 100,000 patients. We are proud to be giving our native wildlife a second chance at life. You can visit www.wildlifewarriors.org for more information💚

node.text:
Our #AustraliaZoo wildlife family were honoured to meet @CrashBandicoot! Check out @robertirwinphotography getting crashed as he got hands on with the new game ‘Crash Bandicoot 4: It’s About Time.’ He even introduced Crash to his cousin, the bilby! ‬
‪#Crash4 #spon‬

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Australia Zoo on July 23, 2021 tagging @bindisueirwin. May be an image of 2 people, outdoors and text that says 'Croc One'.

node.text: Tomorrow is @BindiSueIrwin’s first birthday as a mother💕 She has inspired the world with her kindness and passion for making the world a better place. We are so excited to celebrate Bindi with croc feeding, free admission for kids 14 & under, and free ice cream for everyone!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia Zoo on July 22, 2021. May be an image of wading bird and nature.

node.text: Accurate depiction of our mood when we found out that Brisbane will be hosting the 2032 Olympic Games. 🎉 Our #AustraliaZoo feathered friends are joining in on all the celebrations!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Australia Zoo on July 22, 2021. May be an image of wading bird and nature.
Photo by Australia Zoo on July 22, 2021. May be an image of wading bird and nature.
Photo shared by Australia Zoo on July 21, 2021 tagging @bindisueirwin. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: Only a few days until @BindiSueIrwin’s birthday celebration here at #AustraliaZoo. Join us on Saturday, the 24th, fun-filled day of croc feeding, free ice cream and free admission for kids 14 & under. We’ll see you here!🎉

node.text: Wishing the happiest birthday to our ultimate Wildlife Warrior, Terri! Your strength and perseverance has lead #AustraliaZoo and @wildlifewarriorsworldwide to accomplish milestones in the world of wildlife conservation. Thank you for working every single day to ensure Steve's passion and legacy continues. We love you! 💖

node.text: Things don't quite go to plan for Robert on a routine drone flight. He joins us to run through what went wrong and the recovery mission that followed.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Australia Zoo on July 14, 2021 tagging @wildlifewarriorsworldwide. May be an image of echidna.

node.text: “You are so adorable, Frances! 💚 This sweet echidna was involved in a car accident, causing injuries to the spines near her tail. Our expert vet team at the #AustraliaZoo Wildlife Hospital treated her with specialised medication, and Frances is now recovering with a dedicated wildlife carer who will look after her until she is recovered and ready to get back out in the wild. 🥰🌸” - @wildlifewarriorsworldwide #repost

node.text: We’re proud to be giving wildlife in need a second chance at life with our #AustraliaZooWildlifeHospital 💚 With well over 100,000 patients admitted through our doors, just like this gorgeous koala joey, entire native species are being given a helping hand.🐨
